<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ861216-0064 </DOCNO><HL> Financing Business:Blasius Industries</HL><DD> 12/16/86</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> BLASBOND MARKET NEWS (BON)STOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK) </IN><TEXT>   BLASIUS INDUSTRIES INC. said it postponed until January offerings for at least $35 million in debentures, stock and warrants originally scheduled for completion in December. Blasius seeks to raise at least $30 million by the sale of subordinated debentures, and at least $5 million in new equity by a rights offering to common stockholders in which they will be entitled, for each share owned, to buy an additional share for $2. The new record date is Dec. 31. Blasius, based in Erie, Pa., makes modular office systems, factory partitions and rubber and metal parts for manufacturing. </TEXT></DOC>